An interactive model
The reason this site isn’t on Substack. A Solow-style growth model: capital per worker accumulates as

k_{t+1} = s\,k_t^{\alpha} + (1 - \delta)\,k_t,
\qquad
k^{*} = \left(\frac{s}{\delta}\right)^{\frac{1}{1-\alpha}},

with output k^\alpha, savings rate s, depreciation \delta, and \alpha = 1/3. Drag the sliders; the trajectory and the steady state k^{*} respond instantly.

viewof s = Inputs.range([0.05, 0.6], {value: 0.3, step: 0.01, label: "Savings rate s"})







viewof delta = Inputs.range([0.02, 0.15], {value: 0.05, step: 0.005, label: "Depreciation δ"})







solow = {
  const alpha = 1 / 3;
  const T = 120;
  let k = 1;
  const path = [{t: 0, k: k}];
  for (let t = 1; t &lt;= T; t++) {
    k = s * Math.pow(k, alpha) + (1 - delta) * k;
    path.push({t: t, k: k});
  }
  return path;
}







kstar = Math.pow(s / delta, 1.5)







Plot.plot({
  width: 660,
  height: 380,
  marginLeft: 50,
  style: {fontSize: "12px"},
  x: {label: "t (periods)"},
  y: {label: "capital per worker, k", grid: true},
  marks: [
    Plot.ruleY([kstar], {stroke: "#b509ac", strokeDasharray: "4 4"}),
    Plot.text([{t: 118, k: kstar}], {
      x: "t", y: "k",
      text: [`k* = ${kstar.toFixed(2)}`],
      dy: -10, fill: "#b509ac", textAnchor: "end", fontWeight: 600
    }),
    Plot.lineY(solow, {x: "t", y: "k", stroke: "#000000", strokeWidth: 1.5})
  ]
})






Later, the same machinery carries anything: a roofline explorer, an attention visualiser, a takeoff model with more dials than anyone needs.
